 A custom exception is a user-defined exception created by the programmer to handle specific business logic errors.
custom exception are the class created by the user by extending the Exception class and the RuntimeException class

why we are using that?
Defalut exception are genrics but in the real project we need the meaningful exception handling messages 
for example :
Invlaid age exception 
Insufficient balance exception
Invalid email exception

How we can create the cusotm exception
step 1:
create the class that extends check or uncheck exception 

class InvalidAgeException extends Exception {
    public InvalidAgeException(String message) {
        super(message);
    }
}

Step 2:
use it with the throw

public class TestCustomException {

    static void checkAge(int age) throws InvalidAgeException {
        if (age < 18) {
            throw new InvalidAgeException("Age must be 18 or above");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Eligible to vote");
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            checkAge(16);
        } catch (InvalidAgeException e) {
            System.out.println(e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}

